{{Primary sources|date=January 2011}} {{Infobox journal | title = Bible and Spade | cover = Bible and Spade.jpg | caption = Cover of Fall 2009 issue | former_name = <!-- or |former_names= --> | abbreviation = Bible Spade | discipline = Biblical Archaeology | peer-reviewed = | language = English | editor = [[Bryant G. Wood]] | publisher = [[Associates for Biblical Research]] | country = United States | history = 1972-current | frequency = Quarterly | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | ISSNlabel = | ISSN = 1079-6959 | eISSN = | CODEN = | JSTOR = | LCCN = | OCLC = | website = http://www.biblearchaeology.org/publications/bibleandspade.aspx | link1 = | link1-name = | link2 = <!-- up to |link5= --> | link2-name = <!-- up to |link5-name= --> | boxwidth = }} '''''Bible and Spade''''' is a quarterly [[magazine]] published by the [[biblical inerrancy|inerrantist]] Associates for Biblical Research, explicitly committed to the use of [[archaeology]] to demonstrate the historical veracity of the [[Old Testament|Old]] and [[New Testament]]s.<ref>{{cite web |title=Bible and Spade Magazine |url=http://www.biblearchaeology.org/publications/bibleandspade.aspx |work=www.biblearchaeology.org |publisher=Associates for Biblical Research |accessdate=11 September 2012}}</ref> The magazine concentrates largely on matters relating to archaeology and Bible history, but also touches on general [[apologetics]] (especially the relationship between science and evangelical religious belief) and Christian devotion.<ref>{{cite web |title=Latest research articles by category |url=http://www.biblearchaeology.org/research.aspx |work=www.biblearchaeology.org |publisher=Associates for Biblical Research |accessdate=11 September 2012}}</ref> The [[editor-in-chief]] is [[Bryant G. Wood]].
