'''Climacturia''' is [[urinary incontinence]] at the moment of sexual climax ([[orgasm]]). It can be a result of radical [[prostatectomy]] to treat [[prostate cancer]]. It is uncomfortable at times, but usually harmless. <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.issm.info/sexual-health-qa/what-is-climacturia/|title=What is climacturia?|website=www.issm.info|access-date=2018-06-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Lee|first=Jason|last2=Hersey|first2=Karen|last3=Lee|first3=Charlotte T.|last4=Fleshner|first4=Neil|date=2006-12|title=Climacturia following radical prostatectomy: prevalence and risk factors|journal=The Journal of Urology|volume=176|issue=6 Pt 1|pages=2562–2565; discussion 2565|doi=10.1016/j.juro.2006.07.158|issn=0022-5347|pmid=17085160}}</ref>
