{{Infobox recurring event | name = Viable Paradise | logo = | logo_caption = | image = | imagesize = | caption = | status = | genre = [[Speculative fiction]] | date = | begins = [[Autumn]] | ends = One week | frequency = Annual | venue = | location = [[Martha's Vineyard]], [[Massachusetts]], U.S. | coordinates = | country = | years_active = | first = {{start date and age|1997}} | founder_name = | last = <!--{{start date|YYYY|mm|dd}} --> | prev = <!-- [[previous event]] --> | next = <!-- [[next event]] --> | participants = | attendance = | area = | budget = | activity = | patron = | organised = | filing = | people = | member = | website = {{URL|viableparadise.com}} | footnotes = }}
'''Viable Paradise''' is an annual one-week residential [[writing workshop]] held each autumn on the island of [[Martha's Vineyard]] in [[Massachusetts]] and is focused on [[speculative fiction]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zanzjan.net/vp/vp-sales.html|title=List of former V.P. students|website=Zanzjan.net}}</ref>
The workshop began in 1997, as part of a science fiction convention presented by the Martha's Vineyard Science Fiction Association. After 1998, the convention was discontinued, but the workshop continued.
Present and past instructors include: [[Patrick Nielsen Hayden]], [[Teresa Nielsen Hayden]], [[James D. Macdonald]], [[Debra Doyle]], [[Steven Gould]], [[Laura J. Mixon]], [[Lawrence Watt-Evans]], [[Elizabeth Moon]], [[Maureen McHugh]], [[James Patrick Kelly]], [[Elizabeth Bear]], [[Cory Doctorow]], [[John Scalzi]], [[Sherwood Smith]], [[Steven Brust]], [[Daryl Gregory]], and [[Scott Lynch]].
Past students include authors [[Curtis C. Chen]], [[Julie C. Day]], [[Claire Humphrey]], [[N. K. Jemisin]], [[Marko Kloos]], [[Fonda Lee]], [[Sandra McDonald]], [[Paul Melko]], [[David Moles]], [http://www.harpercollins.com/author/microsite/about.aspx?authorid=34313 Margaret Ronald], [[Greg van Eekhout]], and [[Fran Wilde (author)|Fran Wilde]]; and podcast editors and authors Serah Eley and [[Mur Lafferty]].
